</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Coca-Cola Amatil, the Australian-based soft drinks company controlled by
Coca-Cola in the US, is acquiring a 75 per cent interest in the former
state-owned enterprise which holds the Coca-Cola franchise in the Republic
of Slovenia. The deal is worth about ADollars 10m (USDollars 7.1m).
Coca-Cola said the business, which is being privatised, will manufacture and
distribute Coca-Cola products through an existing bottling plant in Zalec,
and a sales and distribution depot in Ljubliana. The remaining equity in the
business will be held locally, essentially by employees.
Coca-Cola Amatil already has franchises in surrounding countries, including
Austria, Hungary, the Czech and Slovak republics and Belarus.
Amcor, the Australian paper and packaging group which has been expanding
aggressively into Europe and North America, yesterday announced plans to
build an ADollars 18m flexible packaging plant in Beijing. The project is
aimed mainly at servicing multinational customers with established
operations in the region.
The company said construction would start shortly, and that the plant was
due to be operational by mid-1995.
