FT  31 MAR 94 / Tighter planning controls announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government yesterday announced tighter planning controls on houses in
conservation areas.
The proposals will give wider powers to local planning authorities wanting
to restrict homeowners' ability to make changes to the outside appearance of
their properties. Authorities will be required to publicise their proposals
in advance and pay regard to the views of local people.
The measures are a response to last July's consultation paper on the
protection of conservation areas issued by the environment and national
heritage departments.
