</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
House prices on average rose 0.6 per cent last month compared with February,
said Nationwide, Britain's second-largest building society, Andrew Taylor
writes.
It said yesterday that the average price of a UK house had risen by 2.8 per
cent to Pounds 53,751 since March 1993.
Mr Brian Davis, Nationwide's operations director, said: 'There is little
sign that tax increases due to take effect in April are having an influence
on the housing-market recovery.
'Market turnover in the early part of the year is up substantially on the
same period of 1993 while current indications are that the stronger trend in
mortgage lending apparent over recent months is being maintained,' he said.
