<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAR 94 / German ban on beef dismissed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
European Union health ministers yesterday dismissed German attempts to
impose a ban on UK beef exports.
Mr Horst Seehofer, the German health minister, replied by threatening to
seek a unilateral ban from his government, but his support has yet to be
tested. He had sought a ban on exports of live cattle and beef from the UK,
arguing that bovine spongiform encephalopathy - 'mad cow disease' - could
enter the food chain.
Brussels made clear once more that it would take legal action if Germany
attempted to impose a unilateral ban.
</TEXT>
