FT  31 MAR 94 / China cautious over N Korea
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China proposed to its United Nations Security Council colleagues yesterday
that they issue a mildly worded statement urging North Korea to allow
unhampered inspection of its nuclear facilities, Reuter reports from New
York. The proposed text would not include any threat of sanctions if North
Korea continued to baulk. The Chinese indicated they were opposed to an
alternative plan, favoured by the US, UK, France and Russia, to pass a
resolution aimed at North Korea.
Security Council President Jean-Bernard Merimee of France Merimee said he
still expected a resolution to be put to the vote today. He believed China
would abstain rather than veto it. While a resolution would carry greater
weight than a Security Council statement, a Chinese abstention would weaken
the message conveyed to North Korea.
