FT  31 MAR 94 / Ten die in French N-submarine
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MARSEILLES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ten sailors were killed yesterday in an explosion on board a French nuclear
submarine off the Mediterranean port of Toulon, defence ministry officials
said. The 2,400-tonne attack submarine Emeraude, of the Rubis class, was
taking part in a training exercise. A navy spokesman, Captain Olivier
Lajous, said the accident did not affect the submarine's nuclear engine, it
was was not carrying nuclear missiles and there was no risk of radiation.
'One of the two turbo alternators, which generate electrical power on board,
exploded while the submarine was off the coast. We don't know why,' Capt
Lajous said. The submarine was making its way to Toulon unassisted.
