</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PLO leaders in Gaza emphatically denied yesterday that the six Fatah
activists shot dead by Israeli undercover troops in the Jeblaya refugee camp
on Monday night had opened fire first on the soldiers, and Israeli military
officials appeared to backtrack on their earlier claims that the soldiers
had come under fire.
