group turnover fell 37 per cent to MDollars 136m.
Renong, once a diversified group with interests in many areas of the
Malaysian economy, has recently been focusing on infrastructure
developments.
United Engineers Malaysia, the Malaysian construction and engineering
company in which Renong has a controlling stake, has announced pre-tax
profits for the year ending December 31 1993 of MDollars 237m, an increase
of 18 per cent over the 1992 figure.
