FT  30 MAR 94 / International Company News: British Gas reviewing oil and
gas holding
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bow Valley Energy, the Calgary-based oil and gas producer, said yesterday
British Gas was reviewing its 53 per cent stake in the company.
British Gas played down the announcement, saying the exercise is part of an
overall review of its international operations. However, Bow Valley said it
had supplied confidential information on its operations to not only to
Britis Gas, but also to unspecified third parties.
Bow Valley said British Gas had made no decision as to whether to dispose of
its investment, which at current market prices, is worth about CDollars 580m
(USDollars 433m).
Mr Duncan Mathieson, analyst at Wood Gundy in Toronto, said a management
shake-up over the past two years had given Bow Valley 'good focus and good
direction'.
The company, whose operations are centred on western Canada, the North Sea
and Indonesia, posted net earnings of CDollars 7.4m last year on revenues of
CDollars 243m. It produces about 24,000 barrels of oil and 162m cubic feet
of gas a day.
